@tablethotels takes a peek at the stunning farmhouse hotels of southern Italy. Tablet is the official hotel selection of the Michelin Guide, and today they're spotlighting what's fast becoming a major travel & food trend in Italy — agricultural tourism.

Aiding in the appeal is the masseria, a type of farmhouse hotel found mostly in the country's southern region of Puglia. At the center of an agricultural estate, these fortified farmhouses were used for centuries as storage sites for food and valuables to protect from foreign raiders. Today, guests enjoy meals within their walls from food produced right on site.

📲 If you're tempted by these hands-on hotel experiences in Italy, learn more about Tablet's accomodations on the new MICHELIN Guide App!

